.TH "WebGLRenderingContext.polygonOffset" "JS" "April 8, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGLRenderingContext.polygonOffset \- WebGLRenderingContext:
polygonOffset() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGLRenderingContext.polygonOffset()\f[B]\f[R] method of
the WebGL API specifies the scale factors and units to calculate depth
values.
.PP
The offset is added before the depth test is performed and before the
value is written into the depth buffer.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
polygonOffset(factor, units)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]factor\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLfloat\f[R] which sets the scale factor for the variable depth
offset for each polygon.
The default value is 0.
.TP
\f[B]units\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLfloat\f[R] which sets the multiplier by which an
implementation\-specific value is multiplied with to create a constant
depth offset.
The default value is 0.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
The polygon offset fill is disabled by default.
To enable or disable polygon offset fill, use the \f[CR]enable()\f[R]
and \f[CR]disable()\f[R] methods with the argument
\f[CR]gl.POLYGON_OFFSET_FILL\f[R].
.IP
.EX
gl.enable(gl.POLYGON_OFFSET_FILL);
gl.polygonOffset(2, 3);
.EE
.PP
To check the current polygon offset factor or units, query the
\f[CR]POLYGON_OFFSET_FACTOR\f[R] and \f[CR]POLYGON_OFFSET_UNITS\f[R]
constants.
.IP
.EX
gl.getParameter(gl.POLYGON_OFFSET_FACTOR); \f[I]// 2\f[R]
gl.getParameter(gl.POLYGON_OFFSET_UNITS); \f[I]// 3\f[R]
.EE
